Analogue to Digital:
-Sampling
-Quantisation

Nyquist Shannon sampling theorem:
-Max freq: f_max
-Sampling rate = 2f_max
-Take samples spaced 1/2f_max apart

Speech:
Sampling: 8KHz sampling rate - 8000 samples per second
Quantisation: 8 bits/sample

Audio CD:
44 KHz
16 bits

Image:
Sampling: Resolution - pixels
Quantisation: 8 bits per colour, 3x8=24 bits

Distance Measure Properties:
-Non-negative: D(a,b)>0
-Reflexive: D(a,b)=0 <=> a=b
-Symmetric: D(a,b) = D(b,a)
-Triangular Ineq: D(a,b)+D(b,c)>=D(a,c)
Direct is faster than going indirectly

Distance Metrics:
-Minkowski Distance:
--L1 - Manhattan Distance
--L2 - Euclidean Distance
--Linf - Chebyshev Distance = max(|x1-y1|,|x2-y2|,..)
-Numerical Time Series
--DTW to account for shifting and scalling. Replaces Euclidean one to one comparison with many to one

DTW(X, Y) = D(x0, y0)+min{DTW(X, REST(Y)), DTW(REST(X), Y), DTW(REST(X), REST(Y))}

Symbolic Distance:
-Semantic
-Syntactic

Hamming Distance
-Same length

Edit Distance:
-Any length. Can do better sometimes on same length than hamming distance

Semantic - WUP:
WUP(C1,C2) = 2N3 / (N1+N2+2N3)

Normalisation:
-Rescaling
-Standardisation
-Scaling to unit length
